# Hydra Project Structure

Hydra is an Electron-based project/issue management application. The project is structured as follows:

## Main Directories

- `src/main/`: Electron main process code
  - `index.ts`: Application entry point
  - `core/`: Core functionality and utilities
  - `handler/`: Event handlers

- `src/renderer/`: Frontend code (React)
  - `src/`: React application source code
    - `components/`: UI components (using Atomic Design pattern)
      - `atoms/`: Basic UI elements including charts
      - `molecules/`: Combined components like cards
      - `organisms/`: Complete UI sections (tabs)
      - `templates/`: Page layout components
      - `pages/`: Page components
      - `layouts/`: Common layout components
    - `routers/`: Routing related code
    - `hooks/`: Custom React hooks
    - `lib/`: Utility libraries
    - `stores/`: Zustand stores for state management
    - `types/`: TypeScript type definitions

- `src/preload/`: Electron preload scripts

## Key Features

- Dashboard with various charts and statistics
- Project management with progress tracking
- Issue tracking and visualization
- Data analytics and reporting

## Tech Stack

- TypeScript
- React 19
- Electron
- TailwindCSS
- Recharts (for data visualization)
- Prisma (database ORM)
- Radix UI (component library)
- Zustand (state management)

## UI Guidelines

- All user-facing text must be in English
- Code comments can be written in Korean or English
- Dark mode support
- Responsive design
